# Sticky headers + list rows

## Never combine these

- Do **not** put `overflow: hidden` on a section/card that also has a `position: sticky` section header and scrolling rows. That clips row chrome (sparklines, red/green `%` pills) into a gap above the header — e.g. BTC appearing above “My Crypto”.

## Sticky `top` must be measured

- When a page has a sticky toolbar (search / filters / jump chips) **above** sticky section headers, publish the toolbar height to a CSS variable via `ResizeObserver` (`useCssVarFromElementSize`) and use it in `top` / `scroll-margin-top`.
- Do **not** hardcode toolbar offsets like `7.25rem` unless they are a fallback default only.

## Opaque sticky headers

- Sticky section headers that sit over list rows must use an **opaque** `background-color: var(--bg-elevated)` (no translucent glass bleed). Rows sliding underneath must not show through.

## Shared patterns

- Markets sections: `.markets-section` + `.markets-section-sticky` + `--markets-toolbar-height`
- Equities / Crypto holdings: `.holdings-sticky-search` + `.holdings-sticky-totals` + `--holdings-search-height`
